title: Launch Roundup – Starship ready for fourth flight, Starliner rescheduled for third attempt, Virgin Galactic to fly VSS Unity for last time
summary: There are now two high-profile missions scheduled in the coming week after a challenging weekend that saw the scrub of another attempt to launch the first crewed Starliner and the announcement that the dearMoon project is canceled. In more positive news, it also confirmed that Chang’e 6 became the first vehicle to land on the moon’s far side.

title: NASA prepares for twin launches of climate science cubesats
summary: NASA is gearing up for back-to-back launches of cubesats designed to provide key data for improving models of the Earth’s climate.

title: Rocket Lab prepares for back-to-back launches for NASA
summary: Rocket Lab is preparing for back-to-back missions for NASA, which will see them launch twice within three weeks from Launch Complex 1...

title: NASA Selects Rocket Lab For Polar Energy Monitoring Missions
summary: NASA has selected Rocket Lab to launch a pair of CubeSats in 2024 as part of the Polar Radiant Energy in the Far-InfraRed Experiment (PREFIRE) mission which aims to closely monitor the energy entering and exiting Earth's polar regions, shedding new light on an area of scientific inquiry that has been shrouded in mystery.

title: Rocket Lab to launch pair of NASA Earth science cubesats
summary: NASA selected Rocket Lab to launch a pair of cubesats in 2024 to monitor energy entering and exiting the polar regions of the planet.

title: NASA Announces Launch Service for Arctic Warming Experiment
summary: NASA has selected Rocket Lab USA Inc. of Long Beach, California, to provide the launch service for the agency’s PREFIRE (Polar Radiant Energy in the Far-InfraRed Experiment) mission, which aims to give researchers a more accurate picture of the energy entering and leaving Earth.
